msContents.summary: First book of Avicenna's medical encyclopedia, comprising an introduction to general knowledge of medicine, anatomy, temperament, and the effect of environment on health and disease. Frequent marginal annotations, some affected by trimming.

supportDesc.foliation: Paper, 321; [1-321], modern foliation in pencil, upper left recto.

scriptDesc.scriptNote: Written in naskh script, by multiple hands; beginning and end (f. 1-40, 310-321) of manuscript written on replacement leaves by a later hand.

origin.p: Written in Persia in the late 14th century.

history.provenance: Ownership stamps, probably 19th century, with Persian characters: a rectangle in purple ink with the name Muṣṭafá Shāh ʻAlāʼī and the title Qānūn added by hand (f. 1r), and a ring in red ink, possibly connected with a member of a ruling family (f. 1r, 109r, 228r, 278r, 321r).
Sold by Sam Fogg Ltd. (London) to Lawrence J. Schoenberg, Oct. 2001.
Deposit by Lawrence J. Schoenberg and Barbara Brizdle, 2012.
